    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, chop your<strong> broccoli</strong> into small florets, discard the stem and leaves</p><p>Cut a<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>piece (or two!) of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A3 paper</p><p>Lay your <strong>broccoli florets</strong> in the middle with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and add to a baking tray</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the broccoli to form a sealed parcel[s] and put the tray in the oven for 12 min or until tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
